  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIt seems that we also need to align the `quarkus.container-image.name` to match.\r\nMore specifically the issue as explained to me was worded: \r\n\r\n`If I choose to override the application name from the pom artefact default using quarkus.openshift.name, then I absolutely have to also set the quarkus.container-image.name to match otherwise I get a Deployment detached from the image that is pushed.`\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a quarkus app with the tool of your choice.\r\n2. Add the `quarkus-openshift` extension to the project.\r\n3. Use `Deploymnet` kind: `quarkus.openshift.deployment-kind=Deployment`.\r\n4. Use a custom name of the manifests: `quarkus.openshift.name=custom-name` \r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe app should be deployed and working\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nApp not starting due to `ImagePullBackOff`.\r\nWith closer inspection we see that the image used makes use of the original name and not the custom one, while the image streams do use the custom one.",
